# Conventional Commit Message Rule

All commit message must follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) format:

```
<type>: <description>

<optional body>
```

## type (required)
- feat: add, adjust or remove API or UI feature
- fix: fix API or UI bug
- refactor: refactor, not affect behavior
- perf: performance optimization
- style: code style adjustment (not affect behavior)
- test: test related
- docs: document related
- build: build, dependency, CI/CD related
- ops: ops, deployment, backup related
- chore: other miscellaneous

## description (required)
- Use English
- Use imperative mood, present tense
- No capital letter at the beginning, no period at the end
- 100 words or less

## body (optional)
- Use English
- If description cannot fully describe, use body to supplement

## Example
- feat: add email notifications on new direct messages
- fix: fix wrong calculation of request body checksum
- refactor: implement fibonacci number calculation as recursion
- style: remove empty line
- chore: init
